'''''Banksia'' sect. ''Oncostylis''''' is one of four sections of [[subgenus]] [[Banksia subg. Banksia|''Banksia'' subg. ''Banksia'']]. It contains those ''[[Banksia]]'' species with hooked [[pistil]]s. All of the species in ''Oncostylis'' also exhibit a top-down sequence of flower [[anthesis]], except for ''[[Banksia nutans]]'' which is bottom-up.

''Banksia'' sect. ''Oncostylis'' is further divided into four series, primarily on the overall shape of the [[inflorescence]]:
* [[Banksia ser. Spicigerae|''Banksia'' ser. ''Spicigerae'']] consists of seven species with [[cylinder (geometry)|cylindrical]] inflorescences.
* [[Banksia ser. Tricuspidae|''Banksia'' ser. ''Tricuspidae'']] contains a single species, ''[[Banksia tricuspis]]''.
* [[Banksia ser. Dryandroideae|''Banksia'' ser. ''Dryandroideae'']] contains a single species, ''[[Banksia dryandroides]]''.
* [[Banksia ser. Abietinae|''Banksia'' ser. ''Abietinae'']] contains 13 species with inflorescences that are [[sphere|spherical]] or nearly so.

All ''Oncostylis'' species are endemic to [[southwest Australia|southwest]] [[Western Australia]], except for two members of series ''Spicigerae'', ''[[Banksia ericifolia]]'' (Heath-leaved Banksia) and ''[[Banksia spinulosa]]'' (Hairpin Banksia), which are endemic to the east coast of [[Australia]].

